{{- define "doer-state-transitions" -}}
{{- if eq .Role "coder"}}

CODER STATE TRANSITIONS:
- IMPLEMENTING_CODE → CODE_READY_FOR_REVIEW (submit for review)
- IMPLEMENTING_CODE → BLOCKED (spec ambiguity, assumption budget exceeded)
- CODE_REJECTED → IMPLEMENTING_CODE (address reviewer feedback, re-submit)
- INTEGRATION_FAILED → IMPLEMENTING_CODE (fix merge conflicts, re-submit)
Stop triggers: spec ambiguity → BLOCKED, assumption budget exceeded → BLOCKED, same rejection reason twice → BLOCKED (escalate)
LIMITS: Iteration and review cycle limits are enforced — task starts fresh attempt when limits reached; BLOCKED on second attempt exhaustion.
{{- else if eq .Role "code-planner"}}

CODE PLANNER STATE TRANSITIONS:
- CODE_PLANNING → CODING_PLAN_TO_REVIEW (submit for review)
- CODE_PLANNING → BLOCKED (spec ambiguity or dependency blocker)
- CODING_PLAN_REJECTED → DRAFT_CODING_PLAN (supervisor re-claims for revision)
{{- else if eq .Role "epic-planner"}}

EPIC PLANNER STATE TRANSITIONS:
- EPIC_PLANNING → EPIC_PLAN_TO_REVIEW (submit for review)
- EPIC_PLANNING → BLOCKED (spec ambiguity or dependency blocker)
- EPIC_PLAN_REJECTED → DRAFT_EPIC_PLAN (supervisor re-claims for revision)
{{- else if eq .Role "us-writer"}}

US WRITER STATE TRANSITIONS:
- WRITING_US → US_READY_FOR_REVIEW (submit for review)
- WRITING_US → BLOCKED (spec ambiguity or dependency blocker)
- US_REJECTED → DRAFT_US (supervisor re-claims for revision)
{{- end}}
{{- end -}}
